title: Lynx
---
A lynx stops Dante in his tracks, forcing him to backtrack.
<<task_start Run>>
<<target Hideout>>

//time day
The morning sun shines on Dante, he was not out of danger yet...
===
title: Lion_and_Wolf
---
Quest Goal - Flee from the Lion and Wolf. #task:flee

===
title: Virgil_Introduction
---
Dante : "Have pity on me, whatever you may be, a shade, a man."

Shade : "Not man; I once was man. Both of my parents came from Lombardy, and both claimed Mantua as native city. I was a poet, born under false and lying gods."

Dante : "Could you be Virgil? The fountain that freely pours so rich a stream of speech!"
As Dante is speaking the unbearable pressure of the shadowed forest numbs his mind, as God asked you, you step in to help clear his mind.

Virgil : "We cannot talk now, the beasts will get to us, let's get moving!"
Activity - Small task to fill-in some words that are also **Cards** (These are unlocks for Dante's and Virgil's skill set and they give more background info for both).

<<task_start Escape Fight>>
===

title: Fight
---

Activity - Small "fight" in turn based to get back player's attention and give him a fun way to get out of the situation using what he has learned.

